1
00:01:51,010 --> 00:01:52,610
母亲哭着说:
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}And the mother cried,{\r}

2
00:01:52,740 --> 00:01:56,610
“这是我看到的我自己，反映在你的眼睛里吗？”
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}"Is this myself I see, reflected in your eyes?"{\r}

3
00:01:57,280 --> 00:01:58,980
女儿说:
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}And the daughter said,{\r}

4
00:01:59,110 --> 00:02:02,690
“我看到的是我，是你的镜子吗？”
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}"Is it me I see, mirrored in yours?"{\r}

5
00:03:03,210 --> 00:03:04,510
海伦娜。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Helena.{\r}

6
00:03:05,450 --> 00:03:07,350
回来。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Come back.{\r}

7
00:03:36,980 --> 00:03:40,350
当你回来时，她会让你做两倍的家务。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}She's going to make you do twice as many chores when you get back.{\r}

8
00:03:40,480 --> 00:03:43,090
我不介意交易。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}I don't mind the trade.{\r}

9
00:03:43,220 --> 00:03:46,220
也许如果我们离开的时间足够长，她会忘记她疯了。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Maybe if we're gone long enough, she'll forget she's mad.{\r}

10
00:03:47,790 --> 00:03:49,320
好。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Okay.{\r}

11
00:03:50,390 --> 00:03:52,700
我们慢慢走，小影子。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}We'll walk slow, Little Shadow.{\r}

12
00:04:30,070 --> 00:04:31,100
它就在这里。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}It was here.{\r}

13
00:04:31,570 --> 00:04:33,040
跑步还是走路？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Running or walking?{\r}

14
00:04:35,740 --> 00:04:39,210
步幅比以前更宽了。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}The strides are wider than before.{\r}

15
00:04:39,340 --> 00:04:42,650
在外面更深。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}And deeper on the outsides.{\r}

16
00:04:48,180 --> 00:04:49,120
它正在运行。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}It was running.{\r}

17
00:04:49,250 --> 00:04:50,720
为什么？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Why?{\r}

18
00:04:52,660 --> 00:04:54,790
因为它害怕什么。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Because it was scared of something.{\r}

19
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:56,390
害怕什么？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Scared of what?{\r}

20
00:04:59,290 --> 00:05:00,530
我们。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Us.{\r}

21
00:05:02,300 --> 00:05:04,870
如果你害怕，
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}If you were afraid,{\r}

22
00:05:05,900 --> 00:05:08,700
逃命，你会去哪里？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}running for your life, where would you go?{\r}

23
00:05:29,460 --> 00:05:31,730
没有人能看到我的地方。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Where no one could see me.{\r}

24
00:06:09,770 --> 00:06:12,430
是时候完成狩猎了。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}It's time you finished the hunt.{\r}

25
00:06:23,710 --> 00:06:24,810
如果我错过了怎么办？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}What if I miss?{\r}

26
00:06:24,950 --> 00:06:27,620
然后我们今晚就饿肚子了。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Then we go hungry tonight.{\r}

27
00:06:42,830 --> 00:06:44,700
我没有发出声音。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}I didn't make a sound.{\r}

28
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:48,800
那么，你认为发生了什么？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}So, what do you think happened?{\r}

29
00:06:57,980 --> 00:06:59,020
它闻到了我的味道。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}It smelled me.{\r}

30
00:07:07,220 --> 00:07:08,820
你不需要火。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}You won't need the fire.{\r}

31
00:07:18,670 --> 00:07:21,870
海伦娜，快来拿你今天赚到的钱吧。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Helena, come get what you earned today.{\r}

32
00:07:29,350 --> 00:07:31,410
她总是生我的气。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}She's always mad at me.{\r}

33
00:07:31,580 --> 00:07:35,150
噢，妈不能像我们一样看到幸福。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Oh, your mother can't see happiness like we do.{\r}

34
00:08:45,790 --> 00:08:47,460
好。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Okay.{\r}

35
00:08:47,590 --> 00:08:48,890
我很好。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}I'm fine.{\r}

36
00:08:49,560 --> 00:08:50,960
天色已晚。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}It's getting late.{\r}

37
00:09:10,250 --> 00:09:12,680
海伦娜，没有了。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Helena, no more.{\r}

38
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:58,630
剩下的呢？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Where's the rest of it?{\r}

39
00:09:58,760 --> 00:10:00,130
现在是免费的。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}It's free now.{\r}

40
00:10:02,430 --> 00:10:04,670
它把自己的腿咬掉了？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}It chewed its own leg off?{\r}

41
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:07,700
为了生存，牺牲了它必须付出的一切。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Sacrificed what it had to, to survive.{\r}

42
00:10:59,920 --> 00:11:01,920
我什么时候可以像你一样把我的留在房子里？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}When can I keep mine in the house like you do?{\r}

43
00:11:02,060 --> 00:11:04,590
当你和我一样优秀的猎人时。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}When you're as good a hunter as I am.{\r}

44
00:11:04,730 --> 00:11:05,900
这永远不会。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Which will be never.{\r}

45
00:11:11,030 --> 00:11:12,540
标记说明了什么？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}What do the marks say?{\r}

46
00:11:12,670 --> 00:11:13,940
他们说，
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}They say,{\r}

47
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:16,110
“当你逃离一只愤怒的驼鹿时，
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}"When you're running from an angry moose,{\r}

48
00:11:16,710 --> 00:11:19,540
当心低矮的树枝。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}beware of low branches."{\r}

49
00:12:26,810 --> 00:12:28,110
我听见它在哭。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}I heard it crying.{\r}

50
00:12:29,510 --> 00:12:31,310
她饿了。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}She's starving.{\r}

51
00:12:31,450 --> 00:12:34,920
好吧，我们里面有一些碎片。我们也许可以——
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Well, we have some scraps inside. We could maybe--{\r}

52
00:12:35,050 --> 00:12:37,120
当它们消失时会发生什么？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}What happens when those are gone?{\r}

53
00:12:38,790 --> 00:12:43,230
没有什么比生存的本能更纯粹的了。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}There's nothing more pure than the instinct to survive.{\r}

54
00:12:44,930 --> 00:12:47,100
狼毫不怜悯。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}The wolf holds no pity.{\r}

55
00:12:47,860 --> 00:12:51,400
只是渴望再活一天。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Just the desire to live another day.{\r}

56
00:12:51,530 --> 00:12:55,470
如果你饿死了，你会对狼做什么？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}What would you do to the wolf, if you were starving?{\r}

57
00:12:58,680 --> 00:12:59,910
你是它的猎物。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}You're its prey.{\r}

58
00:13:01,010 --> 00:13:02,780
我们都是。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}We all are.{\r}

59
00:13:10,020 --> 00:13:11,520
但是宝宝呢？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}But what about the baby?{\r}

60
00:13:11,660 --> 00:13:13,620
将独自受苦和死亡。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Will suffer and die alone.{\r}

61
00:13:13,760 --> 00:13:15,390
现在，照我说的去做，海伦娜。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Now, do what I say, Helena.{\r}

62
00:13:19,430 --> 00:13:21,100
-但如果-- -海伦娜，就搬家。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}-But if-- -Helena, move.{\r}

63
00:13:28,900 --> 00:13:31,240
你必须始终保护你的家人。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}You must always protect your family.{\r}

64
00:14:03,340 --> 00:14:06,610
不。这是我独自一人的旅行之一。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Nah. This is one of my alone trips.{\r}

65
00:14:06,740 --> 00:14:09,140
-但我可以帮忙。-不，来吧。你知道规则。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}-But I can help. -No, come on. You know the rules.{\r}

66
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:11,550
我会给你一个惊喜。什么样的惊喜？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}I'll bring you back a surprise. What kind of surprise?{\r}

67
00:14:11,680 --> 00:14:15,590
有点令人惊讶的是，您将不得不等待才能找出它是什么。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Kind of surprise you're gonna have to wait to find out what it is.{\r}

68
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:17,820
现在，回到那里。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Now, get on back there.{\r}

69
00:14:17,950 --> 00:14:19,190
我很快就会回家。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}I'll be home soon.{\r}

70
00:15:40,340 --> 00:15:43,340
对不起，骑在你身上。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Sorry to come ridin' in on you.{\r}

71
00:15:47,240 --> 00:15:48,610
你的妈妈或爸爸在身边吗？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Is your mom or dad around?{\r}

72
00:15:53,420 --> 00:15:54,680
嘿。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Hey.{\r}

73
00:15:54,820 --> 00:15:56,990
希望我没有擅自闯入或做任何事情。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Hope I'm not trespassing or anything.{\r}

74
00:15:57,820 --> 00:15:59,720
不知道有人住在这里。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Didn't know anybody lived way out here.{\r}

75
00:16:01,830 --> 00:16:04,460
出去了几个小时，我都转了一圈。我--
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Been out for hours, and I got all spun around. I--{\r}

76
00:16:04,590 --> 00:16:06,660
我找不到回去的路。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}I can't find my way back to the trail.{\r}

77
00:16:09,430 --> 00:16:11,430
这里任何地方都没有信号。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}No signal out here anywhere.{\r}

78
00:16:12,740 --> 00:16:14,640
听着，如果你能指点我——
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Look, if you could just point me toward--{\r}

79
00:16:14,770 --> 00:16:16,040
説明！
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Help!{\r}

80
00:16:16,170 --> 00:16:18,140
请。在他回来之前。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Please. Before he gets back.{\r}

81
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:20,080
什么？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}What?{\r}

82
00:16:22,140 --> 00:16:23,350
我们在做什么？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}What are we doing?{\r}

83
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:25,010
你在做什么？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}What are-- What are you doing?{\r}

84
00:16:25,280 --> 00:16:26,550
- 上车，海伦娜。-哇。坚持。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}- Get on, Helena. - Whoa. Hang on.{\r}

85
00:16:26,680 --> 00:16:28,180
-他很快就会回来的。-谁？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}-He'll be back soon. -Who?{\r}

86
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:30,390
-拜托，我们得走了。现在！-我--
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}-Please, we have to go. Now! -I--{\r}

87
00:16:30,520 --> 00:16:32,320
-我不想去！-我不能随便带你走。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}-I don't wanna go! -I can't just take you.{\r}

88
00:16:32,450 --> 00:16:33,820
我什至不确定我们在哪里。这就是为什么我——
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}I'm not even sure where we are. That's why I'm--{\r}

89
00:16:41,430 --> 00:16:42,670
不！
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}No!{\r}

90
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:52,540
妈妈！妈妈，住手！
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Mother! Mother, stop!{\r}

91
00:16:53,340 --> 00:16:55,780
妈妈！妈妈，住手！停！
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Mother! Mother, stop! Stop!{\r}

92
00:16:57,110 --> 00:16:58,550
海伦娜！在！
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Helena! No!{\r}

93
00:16:58,680 --> 00:16:59,650
爸爸！
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Father!{\r}

94
00:17:02,650 --> 00:17:04,450
爸爸！
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Father!{\r}

95
00:17:04,590 --> 00:17:06,150
海伦娜？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Helena?{\r}

96
00:17:06,290 --> 00:17:07,790
-爸爸！-海伦娜？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}- Father! - Helena?{\r}

97
00:17:09,160 --> 00:17:10,560
不！
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}No!{\r}

98
00:17:13,160 --> 00:17:14,800
停！停！
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Stop! Stop!{\r}

99
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:29,180
有人！
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Somebody!{\r}

100
00:17:30,310 --> 00:17:32,480
有人！
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Somebody!{\r}

101
00:18:32,910 --> 00:18:34,180
看看谁醒了。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Look who's awake.{\r}

102
00:18:34,980 --> 00:18:36,410
没关系，海伦娜。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}It's okay, Helena.{\r}

103
00:18:37,780 --> 00:18:39,580
妈就在隔壁房间。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Your mother's just in the next room.{\r}

104
00:18:40,280 --> 00:18:41,450
我父亲在哪里？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Where's my father?{\r}

105
00:18:41,580 --> 00:18:45,090
他不在。你现在很安全了。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}He's not here. You're safe now.{\r}

106
00:18:45,220 --> 00:18:47,290
没有什么可害怕的了。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}There's nothing to be afraid of anymore.{\r}

107
00:18:49,420 --> 00:18:50,660
不用担心。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Don't worry about that.{\r}

108
00:19:04,410 --> 00:19:05,640
海伦娜。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Helena.{\r}

109
00:19:07,110 --> 00:19:09,980
我们不应该在这里。我想回家。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}We shouldn't be here. I want to go home.{\r}

110
00:19:10,910 --> 00:19:13,620
-那不是我们的家。-你做了什么？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}-That wasn't our home. -What did you do?{\r}

111
00:19:14,720 --> 00:19:17,590
你做了什么？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}What did you do?{\r}

112
00:19:17,720 --> 00:19:20,590
- 我想要父亲。他不能靠近我们。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}- I want Father. He can't be near us.{\r}

113
00:19:21,690 --> 00:19:22,860
再一次。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Ever again.{\r}

114
00:19:24,860 --> 00:19:26,700
他带走了我，海伦娜。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}He took me, Helena.{\r}

115
00:19:27,860 --> 00:19:28,900
雅 各。。。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Jacob...{\r}

116
00:19:29,730 --> 00:19:32,230
绑架了我，把我带到了树林里。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}kidnapped me and took me to the woods.{\r}

117
00:19:32,370 --> 00:19:33,700
你撒谎。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}You're lying.{\r}

118
00:19:33,970 --> 00:19:37,140
你是个骗子。你一直是个骗子。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}You're a liar. You have always been a liar.{\r}

119
00:19:37,270 --> 00:19:38,680
父亲告诉我。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Father told me.{\r}

120
00:19:40,710 --> 00:19:42,550
别哭了！
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Stop crying!{\r}

121
00:19:42,680 --> 00:19:44,480
你不被允许这样做。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}You're not allowed to do that.{\r}

122
00:19:44,610 --> 00:19:46,580
我们需要让你的母亲休息。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}We need to let your mother rest.{\r}

123
00:19:47,250 --> 00:19:48,550
就几分钟。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Just for a few minutes.{\r}

124
00:19:49,350 --> 00:19:51,690
我们会没事的。海伦娜？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}We'll be okay. Helena?{\r}

125
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:55,320
爸爸？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Father?{\r}

126
00:21:11,830 --> 00:21:13,970
- 谁出局了？-是的。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}- Who's out? - Yeah.{\r}

127
00:21:45,600 --> 00:21:48,370
好吧，我们得走了。加油。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Okay, we have to go. Come on.{\r}

128
00:21:53,580 --> 00:21:55,480
你做得很好。加油。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}You did good. Come on.{\r}

129
00:21:57,450 --> 00:21:59,750
好吧，让我们走这条路。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Okay, let's go this way.{\r}

130
00:21:59,880 --> 00:22:02,720
-他在那儿！-员警！别动！
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}- There he is! - Police! Don't move!{\r}

131
00:22:02,850 --> 00:22:04,290
我们要回家了吗？
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Are we gonna go home?{\r}

132
00:22:04,420 --> 00:22:05,560
总有一天我们会的。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}One day we will.{\r}

133
00:22:05,690 --> 00:22:07,590
嘿！别动！
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Hey! Don't move!{\r}

134
00:22:11,030 --> 00:22:12,230
远离女孩。
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Back away from the girl.{\r}

135
00:22:12,460 --> 00:22:14,530
-不！- 在你的肚子上！
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}- No! - On your stomach!{\r}

136
00:22:14,860 --> 00:22:15,770
现在！
{\fs10\1c&H2DA6EE&}Now!{\r}

137
